[This is the second case born after the controls on animal feed were
implemented; one has also been diagnosed in Northern Ireland. I checked our
postings and the first case was born in May of 1997 (it was in the BSE
update 24 (BSE update (24) June 2001 20010621.1181). - Mod.MP]
[Yahoo.com reported: "This case brings the number of cases of BSE in
animals born after August 1996 to 3 in Britain. One case has also been
diagnosed in Northern Ireland, DEFRA said." Where this information came
from I don't know, as it is not in the DEFRA news release. - Mod.MHJ]
